&lt;h1&gt;Forensic Social Worker, Band 6&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our growing Forensic Social Work Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide a specialist social care service to an agreed caseload of clients and their carers across all areas of the Directorate including the Bracton Centre &amp; Memorial Hospital, community and specialist aftercare aftercare hostel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide advice to multi-disciplinary colleagues regarding social care in the forensic setting and the CMHT setting, support the client&#39;s discharge pathway and Carers, advocate for clients ensuring least restrictive practice, lead on Safeguarding within the MDT, act as a Social Supervisor and inform MDT risk assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Oxleas operates a probationary period, further information is available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCatherine MillarJob titleWomen&#39;s Pathway Senior PratitionerEmail addresscatherine.millar2@nhs.netTelephone number01322 294300Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Women&#39;s Pathway Lead Catherine Millar or Team Manager Shaun Gallagher at the Bracton Centre on 01322 294300.&lt;/p&gt;
